The '''vornskr''' was a canine beast that could hunt using [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. Vornskrs were native to the forest [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]] and hunted the native [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamiri]]. Over time, the ysalamiri developed abilities to suppress the Force as a defensive adaptation against vornskrs.<ref name="The Essential Guide to Alien Species" />

==Description==
[[File:Vornskr_EGF.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Two vornskrs on Myrkr]]
The vornskr, native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]], were a wild, vicious canine species that had the unusual ability to sense [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. This ability evolved to help them hunt [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamiri]], but a side effect caused them to think that [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitives]] were their favorite prey, including [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] in their appetite.

To counteract this hunting method, the ysalamiri developed the ability to project a "Force bubble," which suppressed the amount of Force energy present within, to the point where no Force abilities could be used.

Vornskrs were primarily nocturnal hunters, and used their whip-like, mildly venomous tails to stun prey before finishing it off with their teeth. They were normally sedate during the day, but hunger or other factors would drive them to hunt during daylight hours.

Before [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] refined it into [[Form VII/Legends|''Vaapad'']], the Form VII style of [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]] was referred to as the Way of the Vornskr.

[[Tyber Zann]] used such creatures within the [[Zann Consortium/Legends|Zann Consortium]]. After taking the younger vornskrs away, the pups were trained as effective hunters for enemy troops that escaped imprisonment.

The [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Talon Karrde]] kept two vornskrs, [[Sturm]] and [[Drang]], as pets and guard animals, and considered offering them for sale as guard animals. He discovered that cutting off their whip-like tails was similar to castration, since it removed most of their hunting aggression, a fact he detailed in an article published in the ''[[Galactic Zoology Monthly]]''. Additionally, it made them easier to handle by removing a frequently used weapon. The discovery was a fortunate accident as he had originally shot off Sturm's tail in self defense. Despite being relatively docile, Karrde's vornskr were still instinctively hostile towards [[Force-sensitive/Legends|force users]], such as [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. 

[[File:Vornskr_TotG.jpg|thumb|right|180px|A pack of vornskrs]]
During the [[Peace Brigade]] [[Invasion of Yavin 4|attack]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], Talon Karrde outsmarted the Peace Brigade by leading them into the hands of [[Kam Solusar]] and his wife [[Tionne Solusar|Tionne]]. He achieved this by commanding his two vornskrs to find the Jedi and allowing the Peace Brigaders to follow the trail. Once he found the Jedi, the Peace Brigaders were effortlessly disposed of. During this pretended Jedi hunt, Talon Karrde convinced the Peace Brigaders that he was the owner of the last two remaining vornskrs. The Peace Brigaders seemed to believe him; however, the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] were informed by the traitorous [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Viqi Shesh]] that the vornskrs hailed from [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]]. The Yuuzhan Vong then used the [[Species/Legends|species]] as a biological template for the [[voxyn]].

Vornskrs were also used as guards in the [[Dark Force Temple]] on [[Dromund Kaas/Legends|Dromund Kaas]].

